Create and manage Frappe users.

Examples:
  weg user list                          # List all users
  weg user create test@example.com       # Create a new user
  weg user password Administrator        # Set password
  weg user enable test@example.com       # Enable user
  weg user disable test@example.com      # Disable user
  weg user role add test@example.com "System Manager"

Usage:
  weg user [command]

Available Commands:
  create      Create a new user
  disable     Disable a user
  enable      Enable a user
  list        List all users
  password    Set user password
  role        Manage user roles
  show        Show user details

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for user

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg user [command] --help" for more information about a command.
